objectives.en:
1) Reviewing location theory (agglomeration, accessibility, hierarchy), theories of regional growth at constant returns to scale (production structure and development, demand, factor endowment); theories of local development (territorial competitiveness, exogenous and endogenous development models, endogenous development models including proximity, innovation, and culture); theories of regional development at increasing returns to scale (space as a source of increasing returns);
2) to provide an overview of the principles of regional policy in accordance with development theories and experiences in different regions; and
3) to explain the economic treatment of culture and the role of cultural differences in economic development.
